mming <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Sirocco</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> again lately and using it.<br>
<br>
With <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Spell Casting Master 3</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and 50% <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Specialization: Evocation</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, the mana cost is reduced by 12.5%, or better than 200% <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Spec: Evoke</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and no <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> SCM</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  The resist rate seems quite acceptable, and it is a nice tool.  Under the right circumstances, it appears to still be the most efficient DD spell we have, even with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> 200 Spec: Conj</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Goes well with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Boots of Bladecalling</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, as both generate little aggro.<br>
<br>
Anyway, that is why I read these boards, to get new ideas and observations.<br>
