 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usuzannadreamingheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SuzannaDreamingheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#333333>(7/4/02 9:03:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1361.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: ArchMage Spec: Evoke Sirocco vs. Spec: Conj SoFB</span><hr size=1> Hello <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Yes, I am the guilty one who threw the virtual gauntlet down that started this thread. I noticed it when it was first posted, and decided to carry out my own experiment on this subject, to look at the average damage done by Sirocco for me soloing in Akheva.<br>
<br>
I have now accumulated logs from about 15-20 hours in Akheva. There is a LOT of text (~10MB), so it will take me some time to process. I expect there will be a few hundred casts of the spell. I will strip out the times when I was not soloing, or was hunting in other places, to end up with a large sample over time.<br>
<br>
When I have the results, I will post them. I am genuinely interested if I am over-rating this spell, or if others are under-rating it.<br>
<br>
/bow<br>
