<br>
Many mages quite reasonably see their primary role as dealing damage, through a combination of pets and damage spells.  Many mages find the role of dispensing <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Rods of Transvergence</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> less than satisfactory, and indeed, under many circumstances, is not necessary, even during raids.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Suzanna</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> has made a choice that works well with her preferred playing style.<br>
<br>
Now, I happend to have made the switch to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Conjuration</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and am a great advocate of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Transvergence</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, as is well known.  If I want to convince <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Suzanna</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Conjuration</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> might still serve her better, then I will do so with reasoned open demonstrations.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Spell Casting Mastery</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> makes the difference between different specializations less important.  50% specialization plus <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> SCM 2</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> gives the same benefit as 200% specialization and no <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> SCM</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  With <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> SCM 3</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, 50% specialization saves 17.5% mana, while 200% saves 25% mana.  Both for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Sirocco</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Rods of Transvergence</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, that amounts to saving either 70 or 100 mana per cast.  Now it becomes a matter of how many casts of each spell per day when the mana remaining matters.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Suzanna</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> has already stated this in her assumptions: she casts 1-3 <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Siroccos</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> per fight.  I doubt she casts nearly as many rods.<br>
<br>
As for experiencing, it is and remains an important activity for archmagi.  Where do those nifty <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> AA</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> skills come from anyway?  I have 41 so far, and am looking forward to more.<br>
<br>
In any case, it is not as if the choice is written in stone.  Less than 20 days ago, I switched from <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Evocation</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, which had served me well, to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Conjuration</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and already I am at 175%.<br>
<br>
Questions were made to be asked, and answered.<br>
