<br>
I contest that this is wrong.  With 1 target DD ~= to rain.  With exectly ( 2 or 4 )targets rain &gt; DD.<br>
<br>
Rains are not limited to 3 waves of 1 hit...<br>
<br>
with 2 mobs, you will get two hits for 2 waves.<br>
with 3 mobs, you will get 3 hits in 1 wave (no true advantage)<br>
with 4 mobs you get 4 hits in 1 wave.<br>
<br>
So when factoring in your damage, Sirrocco under idea situations actually does 2520 pts of damage, not 1890.  Recalculate your math and you will find that even with speculization conjuration rains are more efficient (in idea situations) than any DD.<br>
